				<p><p>I would highly recommend you to go through <a href="http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/stamp/stamp.jsp?arnumber=4084563" rel="nofollow noreferrer">"Improved Techniques for Grid Mapping With Rao-Blackwellized Particle Filters"</a> by Grisetti, Stachniss, and Burgard. There is quite a good implementation of it which can found at the <a href="http://www.openslam.org" rel="nofollow noreferrer">OpenSLAM.org</a>. This website is a gold mine for SLAM algorithms and their implementations. You can learn a lot from there.</p>

<p>The algorithm from the paper, "Improved Techniques in grid mapping with Rao Blackwellized particle filters" is implemented as gmapping (or slam gmapping) and it does precisely what you want. The source code can be found on github.</p>

